            <section class="prose">
              <h2>Conversion formula between microcurie and becquerel</h2>
              <p>
                The becquerel (Bq) is the SI unit of radioactivity and
                represents one nuclear decay per second. The curie (Ci) is an
                older unit based on the activity of 1 gram of radium‑226.
              </p>

              <div class="formula-box">
                <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Exact relationships:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
                  <li>\(1 \text{ Ci} = 3.7 \times 10^{10} \text{ Bq}\)</li>
                  <li>
                    \(1 \text{ µCi} = 10^{-6} \text{ Ci} = 3.7 \times 10^{4}
                    \text{ Bq}\)
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    \(1 \text{ Bq} \approx 2.7027027 \times 10^{-5} \text{
                    µCi}\)
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <h3>From microcurie to becquerel (µCi → Bq)</h3>
              <div class="formula-box">
                <p class="mb-1 font-mono text-sm">
                  \( \text{Bq} = \text{µCi} \times 3.7 \times 10^{4} \)
                </p>
              </div>
              <p><strong>Example:</strong> Convert 2.5 µCi to Bq.</p>
              <div class="formula-box">
                <p class="font-mono text-sm">
                  \( \text{Bq} = 2.5 \times 3.7 \times 10^{4} = 9.25 \times
                  10^{4} \text{ Bq} = 92{,}500 \text{ Bq} \)
                </p>
              </div>

              <h3>From becquerel to microcurie (Bq → µCi)</h3>
              <div class="formula-box">
                <p class="mb-1 font-mono text-sm">
                  \( \text{µCi} = \dfrac{\text{Bq}}{3.7 \times 10^{4}} \)
                </p>
              </div>
              <p><strong>Example:</strong> Convert 1,000,000 Bq to µCi.</p>
              <div class="formula-box">
                <p class="font-mono text-sm">
                  \( \text{µCi} = \dfrac{1{,}000{,}000}{3.7 \times 10^{4}}
                  \approx 27.027 \text{ µCi} \)
                </p>
              </div>

